HEADWORD: Mobcap
<hw>Mob"cap`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D.
<ets>mop-muts</ets>; OD. <ets>mop</ets> a woman's coif + D.
<ets>muts</ets> cap.]</ety> <def>A plain cap or headdress for women or
girls; especially, one tying under the chin by a very broad band,
generally of the same material as the cap itself.</def>
<rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

